                                    <h1>Logistics Mobile App Development Cost in India (2026): Complete Pricing Guide</h1>

                                    <p>Building a custom logistics mobile app — for a courier brand, D2C delivery operation, or a fleet operator — in India 2026 typically costs <strong>&#8377;8 lakhs to &#8377;35 lakhs</strong> depending on whether you're shipping a single customer-tracking app or a full ecosystem (customer + driver + dispatcher + admin). This guide breaks the number down line-by-line, based on our live engagements building <a href='../products/logistics-mobile-app.php'>logistics mobile apps</a> for couriers and D2C brands across India, the UAE, the UK and Africa.</p>

                                    <h2>TL;DR — Logistics App Cost at a Glance</h2>

                                    <ul><li><strong>Customer-tracking app only:</strong> &#8377;3.5L–&#8377;6L &middot; 4–6 weeks</li><li><strong>Customer + driver app:</strong> &#8377;8L–&#8377;14L &middot; 6–10 weeks</li><li><strong>Full ecosystem (3 apps + admin):</strong> &#8377;15L–&#8377;25L &middot; 10–14 weeks</li><li><strong>Enterprise (ML routing, multi-hub, SLA-bound):</strong> &#8377;30L–&#8377;45L+ &middot; 16+ weeks</li></ul>

                                    <h2>What's Inside a Real Logistics App Suite</h2>

                                    <p>A complete logistics platform is rarely a single app. It's three apps plus a dashboard:</p><ul><li><strong>Customer app</strong> — book, track, rate, re-order, manage addresses</li><li><strong>Driver / Rider app</strong> — pickup, hub scan, navigation, POD capture, COD collect, earnings</li><li><strong>Hub / Dispatcher app</strong> — manifest, sort, in/out scan, exception flags</li><li><strong>Admin dashboard</strong> — fleet view, dispatch, KPI analytics, billing reconciliation</li></ul><p>Skip any one of these and you'll regret it within 90 days of launch. The customer app drives perception; the driver app drives operational speed; the dispatcher app prevents lost shipments; the dashboard makes the business legible.</p>

                                    <h2>Cost Drivers in Detail</h2>

                                    <p>Five variables move the price:</p><ol><li><strong>Number of platforms</strong> — Android-only is 30–40% cheaper than Android+iOS. iOS is non-negotiable for D2C consumer-facing.</li><li><strong>Real-time tracking architecture</strong> — Polling-based is &#8377;1L cheaper but UX-poor; WebSocket-based scales to 50,000+ daily shipments.</li><li><strong>Number of integrations</strong> — Shiprocket, Razorpay, Google Maps, WhatsApp Cloud API, ERP/WMS — each adds &#8377;30k–&#8377;1.5L.</li><li><strong>Branded vs white-label</strong> — A 100% white-label / OEM-style brand build adds &#8377;1.5L–&#8377;3L over generic skin.</li><li><strong>Offline mode</strong> — Critical for last-mile in poor connectivity zones. Adds &#8377;1.5L–&#8377;3L but pays back fast in operational reliability.</li></ol>

                                    <h2>Module-Level Cost Sheet (India, 2026)</h2>

                                    <table style='width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:18px 0;'><thead><tr style='background:#fff1e6;'><th style='padding:10px;text-align:left;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Module</th><th style='padding:10px;text-align:left;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Cost</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Customer app (Android + iOS)</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;4L – 6L</td></tr><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Driver / rider app</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;3L – 4.5L</td></tr><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Hub dispatcher app</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;2L – 3L</td></tr><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Admin web dashboard</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;3L – 4.5L</td></tr><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Backend + APIs + real-time</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;2.5L – 4L</td></tr><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>Integrations (maps, payments, comms)</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;1L – 2L</td></tr><tr><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>QA + security audit + store launch</td><td style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #f0d9c8;'>&#8377;1L – 1.5L</td></tr></tbody></table>

                                    <h2>Build vs Buy: SaaS CMS vs Custom Logistics App</h2>

                                    <p>SaaS courier management platforms (Shipsy, Loginext, Fareye) start at &#8377;4–7 lakhs/year for the platform plus per-shipment fees. A productised platform like our <a href='../products/courier-management-software.php'>Courier Management Software</a> sits in the middle: faster launch, predictable cost, and 100% source-code ownership available on upgrade.</p><p>Custom builds make sense once your shipment volume crosses ~3,000/day or you need workflows the SaaS platforms can't bend to. See our deeper analysis: <a href='../compare/custom-vs-white-label-courier-software.php'>Custom vs White-Label Courier Software comparison</a>.</p><p><strong>Why founders pick ITD GrowthLabs for logistics builds:</strong> 200+ logistics deployments, 50M+ shipments handled across our platforms, <a href='../products/courier-management-software.php'>a productised CMS</a> and <a href='../products/logistics-mobile-app.php'>a logistics mobile app suite</a> that cut 60–70% of the build time. You don't pay us to learn courier ops on your project — we already know hub manifests, COD reconciliation, scan exceptions and surge dispatch.</p>

                                    <h2>Hidden Costs You Should Budget From Day One</h2>

                                    <ul><li><strong>Maps API:</strong> &#8377;30k–&#8377;1L/month at scale</li><li><strong>SMS + WhatsApp:</strong> &#8377;0.15–&#8377;0.50 per message; OTPs and tracking updates add up</li><li><strong>Cloud hosting:</strong> &#8377;25k–&#8377;1L/month based on shipment volume</li><li><strong>App-store fees:</strong> Apple $99/year; Google Play $25 one-time</li><li><strong>Maintenance retainer:</strong> &#8377;30k–&#8377;1L/month for bug fixes + minor features</li></ul>

                                    <h2>Timeline From Sign-Off to Launch</h2>

                                    <ol><li><strong>Weeks 1–2 — Discovery, brand, wireframes</strong></li><li><strong>Weeks 3–7 — Parallel app development sprints</strong></li><li><strong>Weeks 8–10 — Integration + QA + load testing</strong></li><li><strong>Weeks 11–12 — Pilot + fixes</strong></li><li><strong>Weeks 13–14 — Store launch + go-live support</strong></li></ol><p>For a deeper look at logistics platform engineering, see our <a href='../industries/logistics.php'>logistics industry page</a>.</p>

